import seaborn as sns
import pandas as pd
import matplotlib.pyplot as plt

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    sns.histplot(data=data, x='count', kde=True)
    plt.axvline(data['count'].median(), color='red', label='Median: {:.2f}'.format(data['count'].median()))
    plt.legend()
    plt.title('What is the distribution of flight counts between origin and destination airports?', wrap=True)
    return plt;

chart = plot(data)

import seaborn as sns
import pandas as pd
import matplotlib.pyplot as plt

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    data['distance'] = pd.to_numeric(data['distance'], errors='coerce')
    sns.boxplot(x=data['distance'])
    plt.axvline(x=data['distance'].mean(), color='r', linestyle='--', label='Mean distance: {:.2f}'.format(data['distance'].mean()))
    plt.title('What is the average distance between origin and destination airports?', wrap=True)
    plt.legend()
    return plt;

chart = plot(data)

import seaborn as sns
import pandas as pd
import matplotlib.pyplot as plt

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    data = data.sort_values(by='count', ascending=False)
    chart = sns.barplot(x='origin', y='count', data=data, palette='Blues_d')
    chart.axhline(y=data['count'].max(), color='red', linestyle='--', label=f"Max: {data['count'].max():,.2f}")
    chart.set_xticklabels(chart.get_xticklabels(), rotation=90)
    chart.set(xlabel='Origin Airport', ylabel='Number of Flights')
    chart.legend()
    return chart

chart = plot(data)
